cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.DS

This paper is primarily focused on neural networks and their implementation on computing substrates, which falls under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the use of reservoir computing, which is a subfield of machine learning and falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of dynamical systems and their properties in implementing convolutional neural networks suggests a connection to cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also discusses the improvement in accuracy achieved by the proposed method, which suggests a connection to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the use of time-delay reservoirs and their extension to deep networks suggests a connection to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
